/user-guide","type":"text","url":"/getting-started/user-guide#beyond-the-terminal","content":"Pick CLI for scripts and CI, Web for exploratory UI and simple HTTP automation, MCP when an assistant should drive hyper-pm from chat."},"602":{"id":"/getting-started/user-guide-19","page_id":"/getting-started/user-guide","type":"text","url":"/getting-started/user-guide#json-vs-text-output","content":"The default is --format json, which is ideal for scripting and tools like jq."},"603":{"id":"/getting-started/user-guide-20","page_id":"/getting-started/user-guide","type":"text","url":"/getting-started/user-guide#json-vs-text-output","content":"For interactive use, put --format text (and any other global options) before the subcommand:"},"604":{"id":"/getting-started/user-guide-21","page_id":"/getting-started/user-guide","type":"text","url":"/getting-started/user-guide#planning-model","content":"Epic → Story → Ticket is the usual hierarchy. Tickets can also exist without a story (ticket create without --story)."},"605":{"id":"/getting-started/user-guide-22","page_id":"/getting-started/user-guide","type":"text","url":"/getting-started/user-guide#planning-model","content":"Statuses for epics, stories, and tickets use the same set: backlog, todo, in_progress, done, cancelled (see Data model)."},"606":{"id":"/getting-started/user-guide-23","page_id":"/getting-started/user-guide","type":"text","url":"/getting-started/user-guide#planning-model","content":"Soft deletes remove items from normal reads but stay in the event log for auditability."},"607":{"id":"/getting-started/user-guide-24","page_id":"/getting-started/user-guide","type":"text","url":"/getting-started/user-guide#start-a-new-initiative","content":"hyper-pm init (once per repo)."},"608":{"id":"/getting-started/user-guide-25","page_id":"/getting-started/user-guide","type":"text","url":"/getting-started/user-guide#start-a-new-initiative","content":"Create an epic, then stories under it, then tickets under a story (or standalone tickets)."},"609":{"id":"/getting-started/user-guide-26","page_id":"/getting-started/user-guide","type":"text","url":"/getting-started/user-guide#start-a-new-initiative","content":"Run hyper-pm doctor after upgrades or if anything feels off."},"610":{"id":"/getting-started/user-guide-27","page_id":"/getting-started/user-guide","type":"text","url":"/getting-started/user-guide#pick-up-a-ticket","content":"hyper-pm --format text ticket read --status todo (or filter by epic/story — see Tickets)."},"611":{"id":"/getting-started/user-guide-28","page_id":"/getting-started/user-guide","type":"text","url":"/getting-started/user-guide#pick-up-a-ticket","content":"hyper-pm ticket work --id <id> creates a branch, checks it out, sets status to in_progress, and links the branch on the ticket."},"612":{"id":"/getting-started/user-guide-29","page_id":"/getting-started/user-guide","type":"text","url":"/getting-started/user-guide#pick-up-a-ticket","content":"When finished: commit in your normal flow, then hyper-pm ticket update --id <id> --status done (or your team’s convention)."},"613":{"id":"/getting-started/user-guide-30","page_id":"/getting-started/user-guide","type":"text","url":"/getting-started/user-guide#leave-breadcrumbs","content":"ticket comment appends a durable comment (stored as an event). It shows up on ticket read --id in the comments list."},"614":{"id":"/getting-started/user-guide-31","page_id":"/getting-started/user-guide","type":"text","url":"/getting-started/user-guide#leave-breadcrumbs","content":"audit lists raw events for compliance or debugging — see repo, sync & audit."},"615":{"id":"/getting-started/user-guide-32","page_id":"/getting-started/user-guide","type":"text","url":"/getting-started/user-guide#work-with-github","content":"Configure sync mode and repo slug (see Configuration and GitHub sync). Then:"},"616":{"id":"/getting-started/user-guide-33","page_id":"/getting-started/user-guide","type":"text","url":"/getting-started/user-guide#work-with-github","content":"type: warn"},"617":{"id":"/getting-started/user-guide-34","page_id":"/getting-started/user-guide","type":"text","url":"/getting-started/user-guide#work-with-github","content":"Outbound issue creation on GitHub requires a valid epic → story → ticket chain for that ticket. Unlinked tickets are still updated if they already have a linked issue."},"618":{"id":"/getting-started/user-guide-35","page_id":"/getting-started/user-guide","type":"text","url":"/getting-started/user-guide#discovering-flags","content":"The CLI is the source of truth for every flag:"},"619":{"id":"/getting-started/user-guide-36","page_id":"/getting-started/user-guide","type":"text","url":"/getting-started/user-guide#discovering-flags","content":"The docs site mirrors that behavior in Command overview and the per-topic CLI pages."},"620":{"id":"/getting-started/user-guide-37","page_id":"/getting-started/user-guide","type":"text","url":"/getting-started/user-guide#if-something-goes-wrong","content":"hyper-pm doctor — validates log replay."},"621":{"id":"/getting-started/user-guide-38","page_id":"/getting-started/user-guide","type":"text","url":"/getting-started/user-guide#if-something-goes-wrong","content":"Wrong repo? Use --repo <path> (global, before the subcommand)."},"622":{"id":"/getting-started/user-guide-39","page_id":"/getting-started/user-guide","type":"text","url":"/getting-started/user-guide#if-something-goes-wrong","content":"Sync / auth: ensure GITHUB_TOKEN or gh auth login, and GITHUB_REPO or --github-repo / config — see Configuration."},"623":{"id":"/integrations/github-sync","page_id":"/integrations/github-sync","type":"page","content":"GitHub sync","url":"/integrations/github-sync"},"624":{"id":"/integrations/github-sync-0","page_id":"/integrations/github-sync","type":"text","url":"/integrations/github-sync","content":"Outbound and full inbound sync, labels, planning JSON, and PR activity."},"625":{"id":"/integrations/github-sync-1","page_id":"/integrations/github-sync","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/github-sync#modes","content":"Modes"},"626":{"id":"/integrations/github-sync-2","page_id":"/integrations/github-sync","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/github-sync#outbound-behavior","content":"Outbound behavior"},"627":{"id":"/integrations/github-sync-3","page_id":"/integrations/github-sync","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/github-sync#inbound-full","content":"Inbound (full)"},"628":{"id":"/integrations/github-sync-4","page_id":"/integrations/github-sync","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/github-sync#issue-creation-vs-update","content":"Issue creation vs update"},"629":{"id":"/integrations/github-sync-5","page_id":"/integrations/github-sync","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/github-sync#assignees","content":"Assignees"},"630":{"id":"/integrations/github-sync-6","page_id":"/integrations/github-sync","type":"text","url":"/integrations/github-sync#modes","content":"Configuration (and global --sync) selects how much network integration runs:"},"631":{"id":"/integrations/github-sync-7","page_id":"/integrations/github-sync","type":"text","url":"/integrations/github-sync#modes","content":"off — no GitHub API work."},"632":{"id":"/integrations/github-sync-8","page_id":"/integrations/github-sync","type":"text","url":"/integrations/github-sync#modes","content":"outbound — push hyper-pm changes to issues."},"633":{"id":"/integrations/github-sync-9","page_id":"/integrations/github-sync","type":"text","url":"/integrations/github-sync#modes","content":"full — outbound plus inbound comparison and optional PR timeline ingestion for eligible tickets."},"634":{"id":"/integrations/github-sync-10","page_id":"/integrations/github-sync","type":"text","url":"/integrations/github-sync#outbound-behavior","content":"Issue labels include hyper-pm, ticket, plus each ticket label (GitHub’s label length limits apply)."},"635":{"id":"/integrations/github-sync-11","page_id":"/integrations/github-sync","type":"text","url":"/integrations/github-sync#outbound-behavior","content":"Ticket planning (priority, size, estimate, schedule) is embedded in a fenced JSON block after the issue body so full inbound can round-trip fields conservatively (only keys present in the fence participate — older issues without keys are not mass-cleared)."},"636":{"id":"/integrations/github-sync-12","page_id":"/integrations/github-sync","type":"text","url":"/integrations/github-sync#inbound-full","content":"Compares non-reserved labels and the planning JSON fence to the local projection and appends GithubInboundUpdate when something differs."},"637":{"id":"/integrations/github-sync-13","page_id":"/integrations/github-sync","type":"text","url":"/integrations/github-sync#inbound-full","content":"After inbound, for tickets in_progress with linked issues, hyper-pm may load linked PR timelines when bodies reference issues with Refs / Closes / Fixes — appending GithubPrActivity events. This issues extra GitHub API calls per linked PR."},"638":{"id":"/integrations/github-sync-14","page_id":"/integrations/github-sync","type":"text","url":"/integrations/github-sync#issue-creation-vs-update","content":"Creates on GitHub only happen for tickets with a valid epic + story chain."},"639":{"id":"/integrations/github-sync-15","page_id":"/integrations/github-sync","type":"text","url":"/integrations/github-sync#issue-creation-vs-update","content":"Tickets without a story are skipped for creation until you attach --story."},"640":{"id":"/integrations/github-sync-16","page_id":"/integrations/github-sync","type":"text","url":"/integrations/github-sync#issue-creation-vs-update","content":"Tickets that already have a githubIssueNumber are still updated when unlinked (the issue body drops parent ids until you link again)."},"641":{"id":"/integrations/github-sync-17","page_id":"/integrations/github-sync","type":"text","url":"/integrations/github-sync#assignees","content":"Tickets store at most one assignee (GitHub login). Outbound sync sets that user as the issue’s assignee (additional assignees on the issue may be removed). Inbound reads the first assignee when GitHub returns several."},"642":{"id":"/integrations/github-sync-18","page_id":"/integrations/github-sync","type":"text","url":"/integrations/github-sync#assignees","content":"type: warn"},"643":{"id":"/integrations/github-sync-19","page_id":"/integrations/github-sync","type":"text","url":"/integrations/github-sync#assignees","content":"Sync skips entirely when you pass sync run --no-github, when sync is off in config, or when GitHub credentials are missing."},"644":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"page","content":"MCP server (hyper-pm-mcp)","url":"/integrations/mcp-server"},"645":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-0","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"text","url":"/integrations/mcp-server","content":"Model Context Protocol stdio server — install, Cursor and Claude Desktop setup, tool shape, and security."},"646":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-1","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#security","content":"Security"},"647":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-2","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#install-and-build-order","content":"Install and build order"},"648":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-3","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#from-npm-published-packages","content":"From npm (published packages)"},"649":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-4","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#from-this-monorepo-development","content":"From this monorepo (development)"},"650":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-5","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#build-the-cli","content":"Build the CLI"},"651":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-6","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#build-the-mcp-server","content":"Build the MCP server"},"652":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-7","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#register-the-server-in-your-editor","content":"Register the server in your editor"},"653":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-8","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#environment","content":"Environment"},"654":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-9","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#tool-hyper_pm_run","content":"Tool: hyper_pm_run"},"655":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-10","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#input-json","content":"Input (JSON)"},"656":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-11","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#example-tool-inputs","content":"Example tool inputs"},"657":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-12","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#output","content":"Output"},"658":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-13","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#cursor","content":"Cursor"},"659":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-14","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#claude-desktop","content":"Claude Desktop"},"660":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-15","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#publishing-maintainers","content":"Publishing (maintainers)"},"661":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-16","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"text","url":"/integrations/mcp-server","content":"hyper-pm-mcp is a stdio Model Context Protocol server. MCP-capable editors and apps (for example Cursor, Claude Desktop) can call a single tool, hyper_pm_run, which spawns the same hyper-pm CLI you would run locally."},"662":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-17","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"text","url":"/integrations/mcp-server","content":"Use it when you want an AI assistant to read epics, list tickets, run doctor, or drive sync, without hand-copying JSON between chat and the terminal."},"663":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-18","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"text","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#security","content":"type: warn"},"664":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-19","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"text","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#security","content":"hyper_pm_run executes real hyper-pm processes with the arguments the model supplies (within the JSON schema). Only enable this server in trusted MCP configurations, and keep tokens out of shared project files."},"665":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-20","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"text","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#from-npm-published-packages","content":"The npm package name is hyper-pm-mcp. It lists hyper-pm as a dependency so the CLI is installed next to the server."},"666":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-21","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"text","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#from-npm-published-packages","content":"Point your MCP host at the hyper-pm-mcp binary from the global install (see which hyper-pm-mcp on Unix), or at the resolved path to dist/main.mjs inside the package directory."},"667":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-22","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"text","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#register-the-server-in-your-editor","content":"Use node with the absolute path to apps/hyper-pm-mcp/dist/main.mjs (see examples below)."},"668":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-23","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"text","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#environment","content":"Optional variables are in apps/hyper-pm-mcp/env.example and parsed through @workspace/env."},"669":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-24","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"text","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#environment","content":"Variable"},"670":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-25","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"text","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#environment","content":"Purpose"},"671":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-26","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"text","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#environment","content":"HYPER_PM_CLI_PATH"},"672":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-27","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"text","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#environment","content":"Absolute path to hyper-pm/dist/main.cjs when require.resolve(\"hyper-pm\") is not sufficient (unusual for published installs)"},"673":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-28","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"text","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#environment","content":"The child CLI inherits the host process environment: set GITHUB_TOKEN, GITHUB_REPO, HYPER_PM_AI_API_KEY, etc. in the MCP env object (or system environment) so sync and AI flags work the same as in a terminal."},"674":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-29","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"text","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#tool-hyper_pm_run","content":"Description (for models): runs hyper-pm with JSON output; --format json is always injected by the runner."},"675":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-30","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"text","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#input-json","content":"Aligned with @workspace/hyper-pm-cli-runner (hyperPmRunInputSchema):"},"676":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-31","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"text","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#input-json","content":"Field"},"677":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-32","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"text","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#input-json","content":"Required"},"678":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-33","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"text","url":"/integrations/mcp-