","content":"The tool returns text content: a single JSON document (pretty-printed) with exitCode, signal, stderr, stdout, and parsedStdout (parsed CLI JSON when stdout is valid JSON, otherwise null). The Web UI POST /api/run response uses the same parsing for its json field."},"714":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-69","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"text","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#cursor","content":"Settings → MCP (or your version’s equivalent): add a server entry:"},"715":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-70","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"text","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#cursor","content":"Replace the args path with your machine’s path (global install: path to main.mjs inside node_modules/hyper-pm-mcp if you prefer). Put secrets in env only where your editor stores them safely."},"716":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-71","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"text","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#claude-desktop","content":"Add a similar block under mcpServers in Claude’s config file (location varies by OS; see Anthropic’s MCP docs). Use the same command / args / env pattern as Cursor."},"717":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-72","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"text","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#publishing-maintainers","content":"Publish hyper-pm first, then hyper-pm-mcp, with pnpm publish from each app so workspace: ranges rewrite. Details in apps/hyper-pm-mcp/README.md."},"718":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-73","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"text","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#publishing-maintainers","content":"type: info"},"719":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-74","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"text","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#publishing-maintainers","content":"The Web UI uses the same runner schema for POST /api/run (without repo / tempDir in the body). For human-driven CLI usage, see Examples."},"720":{"id":"/integrations/web-ui","page_id":"/integrations/web-ui","type":"page","content":"Web UI (hyper-pm-web)","url":"/integrations/web-ui"},"721":{"id":"/integrations/web-ui-0","page_id":"/integrations/web-ui","type":"text","url":"/integrations/web-ui","content":"Local browser UI and HTTP API around the hyper-pm CLI — install, env, security, and automation."},"722":{"id":"/integrations/web-ui-1","page_id":"/integrations/web-ui","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/web-ui#what-you-get-in-the-browser","content":"What you get in the browser"},"723":{"id":"/integrations/web-ui-2","page_id":"/integrations/web-ui","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/web-ui#security-defaults","content":"Security defaults"},"724":{"id":"/integrations/web-ui-3","page_id":"/integrations/web-ui","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/web-ui#install-and-run","content":"Install and run"},"725":{"id":"/integrations/web-ui-4","page_id":"/integrations/web-ui","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/web-ui#from-npm-published-packages","content":"From npm (published packages)"},"726":{"id":"/integrations/web-ui-5","page_id":"/integrations/web-ui","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/web-ui#from-this-monorepo-development","content":"From this monorepo (development)"},"727":{"id":"/integrations/web-ui-6","page_id":"/integrations/web-ui","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/web-ui#build-the-cli","content":"Build the CLI"},"728":{"id":"/integrations/web-ui-7","page_id":"/integrations/web-ui","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/web-ui#configure-optional","content":"Configure (optional)"},"729":{"id":"/integrations/web-ui-8","page_id":"/integrations/web-ui","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/web-ui#start-the-app","content":"Start the app"},"730":{"id":"/integrations/web-ui-9","page_id":"/integrations/web-ui","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/web-ui#github-sync-and-ai-helpers","content":"GitHub sync and AI helpers"},"731":{"id":"/integrations/web-ui-10","page_id":"/integrations/web-ui","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/web-ui#http-api","content":"HTTP API"},"732":{"id":"/integrations/web-ui-11","page_id":"/integrations/web-ui","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/web-ui#get-apihealth","content":"GET /api/health"},"733":{"id":"/integrations/web-ui-12","page_id":"/integrations/web-ui","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/web-ui#post-apirun","content":"POST /api/run"},"734":{"id":"/integrations/web-ui-13","page_id":"/integrations/web-ui","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/web-ui#publishing-maintainers","content":"Publishing (maintainers)"},"735":{"id":"/integrations/web-ui-14","page_id":"/integrations/web-ui","type":"text","url":"/integrations/web-ui","content":"hyper-pm-web is a small local server that serves a browser UI and an HTTP API. Every action still runs the same bundled hyper-pm binary as the CLI, so behavior, data, and GitHub sync match what you get in the terminal."},"736":{"id":"/integrations/web-ui-15","page_id":"/integrations/web-ui","type":"text","url":"/integrations/web-ui","content":"Use it when you prefer clicking and forms over shell flags, or when you want a stable POST /api/run endpoint for scripts (with the server fixing repo and temp paths)."},"737":{"id":"/integrations/web-ui-16","page_id":"/integrations/web-ui","type":"text","url":"/integrations/web-ui#what-you-get-in-the-browser","content":"The UI is organized in a sidebar, roughly:"},"738":{"id":"/integrations/web-ui-17","page_id":"/integrations/web-ui","type":"text","url":"/integrations/web-ui#what-you-get-in-the-browser","content":"Overview — high-level view of the managed repo."},"739":{"id":"/integrations/web-ui-18","page_id":"/integrations/web-ui","type":"text","url":"/integrations/web-ui#what-you-get-in-the-browser","content":"Epics, Stories, Tickets — list, open, create, edit, and delete work items (same semantics as CLI CRUD)."},"740":{"id":"/integrations/web-ui-19","page_id":"/integrations/web-ui","type":"text","url":"/integrations/web-ui#what-you-get-in-the-browser","content":"Tools — utilities that still go through the CLI."},"